Second, PSM enhances the interpretability of results by controlling for con-
founding variables, such as firm size, profitability, leverage, and market dy-
namics, which might otherwise obscure the relationship between board size and
outcomes. By improving the comparability of treatment and control groups,
PSM strengthens the reliability and validity of the findings, making it an
invaluable tool in observational research (Lennox et al., 2012; Rosenbaum and
Rubin, 1983).
